(a)  Five or more residents of this State who share a common bond may file an application with the commissioner to engage in the business of a credit union. 	(b)  The application shall contain the following information, unless waived by the commissioner:



	(1)	The proposed name of the credit union;
	(2)	Proposed lease agreements for its principal office;
	(3)	The territory in which the proposed credit union will operate;
	(4)	A business plan;
	(5)	Employment history, education, management experience and other biographical information for all original chartering applicants, and proposed executive officers of the credit union;
	(6)	Proposed policies regarding loans, investments, operations, accounting, recordkeeping and applicable federal and state consumer laws; and
	(7)	Any other information that the commissioner may require.



	(c)  The application shall be submitted on a form prescribed by the commissioner.  The application shall be accompanied by a fee as the commissioner shall establish by rule, no part of which shall be refundable. [L 1993, c 350, pt of §1]
